name: Nike SB Dunk Low Hayley Wilson
Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome Matcha

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome Matcha brings a fresh, nature-inspired take to a classic skateboarding silhouette. Inspired by the shades of green found in matcha, this sneaker blends earthy tones across its premium suede and leather upper. Deep legion green and burnt sienna accents add contrast, while the light khaki base keeps the design grounded and wearable.

Designed with skaters in mind, the sneaker features a padded collar for extra ankle support, a durable rubber outsole for superior grip, and responsive cushioning for impact protection. Yuto Horigome’s signature details are subtly placed throughout, honoring his influence in the skateboarding world.

Releasing on April 5, 2025, the Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome Matcha retailed for $135. Whether you’re hitting the skatepark or just looking for a unique colorway, this Dunk Low offers style and performance in equal measure.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Rodeo Tourmaline

details.description: Introducing a stylish and versatile addition to your wardrobe. This product combines contemporary design with superior craftsmanship, offering both comfort and durability for everyday wear. Crafted from high-quality materials, it features attention to detail in every aspect, from the stitching to the finish, ensuring a premium look and feel. The product's sleek silhouette and thoughtful design elements make it suitable for various occasions, whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual for a day around town. Its versatility is matched by its practicality, with functional features that enhance its usability without compromising on style. Our team of experts particularly loves this product for its ability to elevate any outfit while providing lasting comfort and quality that stands the test of time.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field is a stunning homage to the timeless 1939 classic The Wizard of Oz. Inspired by the iconic poppy field scene where Dorothy and her friends fall under its magical spell, this sneaker transforms vivid storytelling into wearable art. Its unique design features a special print showcasing a floral tapestry of orange, red, yellow, green, and black, bringing the vibrant poppy field to life.

True to Nike SB’s legacy, the Poppy Field Dunk Low blends nostalgic details with contemporary craftsmanship. The heel features Dorothy’s legendary line, "There’s no place like home," embroidered in bold lettering. A second hidden layer of red leather peeks through the upper for added depth, while custom insoles include an image of the Wicked Witch of the West, making these sneakers a collector’s dream. Satin finishes, a lush red outsole, and the iconic "Wizard of Oz" text on the tongue complete the story-driven design.

Set to release on December 23, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Wizard of Oz Poppy Field will retail for $135. Whether you’re a sneaker enthusiast or a fan of the beloved film, this pair masterfully merges cinematic nostalgia with modern skate culture, offering a wearable tribute to Dorothy’s unforgettable journey.

Disclaimer: All blind bags must be opened in order to verify the shoes inside

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro White Gum

details.description:
Nike SB is launching into 2023 with the release of the Nike SB Dunk Gum Pack. Nike’s Gum Pack features the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro in White Gum and Black Gum colorways.

The Nike Sb Dunk Low Pro White Gum is constructed using premium tumbled leather across the uppers, and black nubuck swooshes. The sneakers sit on top of a gum colored outsole, and feature black Nike branding on the heel, tongue, and insoles.
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro White Gum released March 1, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Nike Dunk Low Pro SB Black White Gum

details.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Pro SB Black White Gum is a sleek and stylish addition to the iconic SB Dunk line. Featuring a classic color combination, this shoe boasts a black leather upper with contrasting white accents on the Swoosh, heel tab, and midsole. The gum rubber outsole adds a touch of warmth and provides excellent traction, making it perfect for skateboarding or casual wear.

Designed with both style and functionality in mind, the Nike Dunk Low Pro SB incorporates premium materials and advanced cushioning technology. The padded collar and tongue offer enhanced comfort and support, while the Zoom Air unit in the heel delivers responsive cushioning. The durable construction ensures long-lasting wear, whether you're hitting the skate park or navigating city streets. Us at StockX believe this product is great for skaters and sneaker enthusiasts alike, offering a versatile and timeless design that can elevate any outfit.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro J-Pack Chicago

details.description:
The latest Nike SB Dunk J-Pack Chicago keeps Jordan Brand’s relationship with skateboarding strong. For those that don’t know, before the plethora of options for proper skateboarding footwear, skaters in the 80s and 90s preferred boarding in Air Jordan 1s. The sneaker’s high top construction provided the proper amount of ankle support needed to bare various skateboarding tricks. The recent addition to the Nike SB Dunk J-Pack pays homage to Air Jordan 1’s involvement with early skate culture.

This Nike SB Dunk Low J-Pack Chicago has something that both Jordan and SB heads will enjoy. The classic SB Dunk Low silhouette is dressed in a Chicago Jordan 1 red, white, and black leather colorway. From there, a fat tongue and oval laces introduce the skateboarding aspect of the sneaker.

The Nike SB Dunk Low J-Pack Chicago release in September 2020 for $95. They were re-released in 2024.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low CSEF

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low CSEF showcases an innovative partnership with the College Skateboarding Educational Foundation, combining skate culture with educational advocacy in a striking sneaker. Crafted from a premium medley of patent leather, suede, smooth leather, and mesh, the sneaker's eye-catching palette of summit white, black, iron grey, clear emerald, and bucktan creates a visually captivating experience. Hidden beneath the skate-friendly design, playful features such as a scantron-inspired tongue and a flaming graduation cap graphic bring its educational theme vividly to life.

This sneaker not only celebrates skateboarding's cultural impact but also directly supports student skaters aiming higher academically. With unique elements like the eraser pink layer revealed through wear and CSEF branding proudly on display, it's a conversation starter both on and off the board.

Released on May 3, 2025, the Nike SB Dunk Low CSEF retailed at $125, blending bold style with impactful purpose, making it a must-have for skaters and fashion-forward sneakerheads alike.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards is a stylish collaboration between Nike SB and the California based skate brand, There Skateboards. Dressed in a sleek black, gorge green, and summit white colorway, this Dunk captures the essence of skate culture with its clean lines and minimalist approach. The collaboration reflects the shared values of craftsmanship and authenticity, making this release particularly special for fans of both brands.

The Nike SB Dunk has always been a symbol of the intersection between skateboarding and street fashion, and this partnership with There Skateboards underscores that connection. The design includes premium materials like smooth leather and suede, giving the sneaker both durability and a refined edge. Subtle branding details like the There logo on the tongue and insole make this collaboration distinct while maintaining the timeless appeal of the SB Dunk.

Released on August 6, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards retailed at $135. The black, gorge green, and summit white colorway offers a versatile yet stylish look that’s perfect for skaters and collectors alike. Whether you’re hitting the pavement or just looking to elevate your style, this Dunk offers the ideal mix of function and fashion.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Futura Laboratories Bleached Aqua

details.description:
Step into a world of art and innovation with the Nike SB Dunk Low Futura Laboratories Bleached Aqua. This sneaker is a masterpiece, blending iconic street art with top-tier skateboarding functionality. The canvas upper features a vibrant mix of Bleached Aqua, Geode Teal, and White, adorned with the dynamic strokes and splashes reminiscent of Futura's signature street art. The design reflects a seamless fusion of creativity and urban edge, with Futura's distinctive signature and the "FL" emblem proudly displayed on the heel

Designed for both visual appeal and performance, this collaboration with Futura Laboratories enhances the SB Dunk Low with a lightweight, durable canvas that supports both casual wear and skateboarding demands. The responsive cushioning and stable, low-profile outsole ensure comfort and functionality without compromising the sneaker's artistic flair. It's a tribute to both Futura’s revolutionary artistry and Nike’s commitment to quality.

Released on May 18, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low Futura Laboratories Bleached Aqua retailed for $135. This release captivated both art aficionados and sneakerheads alike, offering a unique piece of wearable art that stands out in any collection. Each step in these sneakers is a step in a modern art gallery, showcasing the enduring legacy of Futura and the innovative spirit of Nike SB.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black

details.description:
Released ahead of Halloween, the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black paints the familiar silhouette in a spooky monochromatic colorway.

Although the Halloween accents are subtle, they make the triple black version of the SB Dunk Low stand out from other models. For example, Nike’s signature orange label, part of the insole, and the care instructions are the only colorful accents on the shoe. They pop against the all-black nubuck on the Swoosh, forefoot, and heel overlays, vamp, eyelets, and heel tab. Completing the dark aesthetic, the laces and rubber outsole also come in black. Perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe, while padding in the tongue and collar protects the ankle.

Our experts like that this sneaker was released only in skate shops, giving the sneaker an exclusive feel. The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black was released on October 1, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Premium City of Style

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Premium City of Style is a low-top version of the basketball shoe that showcases scenes of nature in its design.

This version of the Nike SB Dunk Low Premium has an upper made of high-quality leather. The background is a light gray color with the illustrations outlined in khaki, Flat Gold, and light brown. On the upper you’ll find illustrations of clouds, trees, and graffitied walls containing "SB" branding. The leather overlays and the Nike Swoosh on both sides also contain these illustrations but are outlined in a Flat Gold color to make them stand out. Nike branding can be found stitched in gold on the back of the heel, and a brown/gold Nike SB patch can be found on the tongue. The white sole is patterned for traction.

What we like most about this shoe is the subtle SB branding that appears in the illustrations and is integrated into the overall design. The Nike SB Dunk Low Premium City of Style was released on April 10, 2024, for a price of $125.

Disclaimer: Please be aware that there is a removable top layer material revealing a red layer underneath.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro B Parachute Beige

details.type: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro B
details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro B Parachute Beige is a low-top silhouette with a color-blocking design and extra cushioning for comfort.

This iteration of the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro B is made with a suede upper that is designed to soften and look more vintage with wear. The upper appears completely in a Parachute Beige color, including the base, overlays, and branding elements. The toe box has been perforated for increased air flow. The only deviation from the suede material is around the ankle, where you will find textile material, and the heel collar is white leather with Nike branding. A Nike patch also adorns the tongue. A Parachute Beige midsole and gum rubber outsole complete the look.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the suede material that is designed to gain even more character with wear. The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro B Parachute Beige was released on January 24, 2025, for $125.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low City of Love Light Bone

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Light Bone is a masterpiece of design that captures the essence of Paris, the City of Love, in every stitch and shade. Adorned in a harmonious blend of coconut milk, light bone, phantom, university red, and sail, this sneaker reflects the city’s renowned architecture, elegance, and vibrant culture. Crafted for those who appreciate the subtleties of storytelling through design, this edition brings a piece of Parisian spirit to the world of skateboarding and streetwear.

Drawing inspiration from the limestone facades and the romantic allure that pervades Paris’s streets, the sneaker’s colorway is a nod to both the city’s historic charm and its modern vibrancy. The use of university red accents evokes the passion and love that the city symbolizes, while the detailed construction and choice of materials showcase Nike’s dedication to quality and innovation. It’s a celebration of Parisian creativity, designed for those who navigate the urban landscape with ease and elegance.

Released on February 9, 2024, for $125, the Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Light Bone became an instant icon among sneaker enthusiasts and Francophiles alike.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop is a striking collaboration that pays homage to the vibrant skateboarding culture. This men's sneaker features a rich mahogany base, complemented by dark beetroot, team red, sail, and night maroon accents, creating a visually captivating design. The premium materials and expert craftsmanship ensure both style and durability, making it an ideal choice for skaters and sneaker enthusiasts alike.

Designed with skateboarding in mind, these shoes offer superior comfort and performance. The low-top silhouette provides flexibility and freedom of movement, while the padded collar and tongue offer enhanced support. The shoe comes with both red and black laces, allowing for customization to suit individual preferences. With its unique colorway and attention to detail, the Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop is set to become a coveted addition to any sneaker collection.

Us at StockX believe this product is great for both skateboarding enthusiasts and fashion-forward individuals looking for a versatile, eye-catching sneaker that stands out from the crowd.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster comes toned in a mixture of three main colors: electro orange, orange frost, and white.

This Low Nike SB Dunk features a nubuck upper with varying orange tones, softly speckled overlays, and a tonal Swoosh accented in white. The interior lining is embellished with a bib-inspired pattern, and the white mesh tongue is embellished with a woven Nike SB tag. The shoe boasts an orange rubber outsole and a cupsole with black sidewalls.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster was set to retail at $120 at its market launch on December 20th, 2022.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Big Money Savings

details.colorway: Baroque Brown/Summit White-Sanddrift-Dark Smoke Grey-Paradise Aqua
details.description:
Introducing the Nike SB Dunk Low Big Money Savings, a sneaker that pays homage to the thrifty spirit and celebrates the art of the find. Released on April 17, 2024, these kicks are a perfect match for the crowd with a penchant for vintage vibes and sustainable fashion. Decked in a mix of baroque brown, summit white, sanddrift, dark smoke grey, and paradise aqua, the design mirrors the eclectic array of goods one might discover in antique, vintage and thrift shops.​
​​
​Constructed with a medley of premium materials, the Nike SB Dunk Low tells its unique story through textures that evoke the thrill of thrifting. You'll notice the suede overlays reminiscent of well-worn leathers and rope-textured laces that speak to the craft and quality of past eras. The sneaker's inner tongue features a boldly stated 'BIG MONEY SAVINGS' tag, a playful nod to the unexpected deals and steals found in the hunt for hidden gems.​
​​
​At $125, the Nike SB Dunk Low Big Money Savings is a narrative woven into each thread, inspired by a sustainable choice that resonates with the values of its wearers. It's an invitation to explore the stories behind the style, to embrace the patina of the past, and to make a fashion statement that is as conscious as it is cool.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari

details.description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari is a commemorative sneaker that honors skateboarding at the 2024 Paris Olympics. It features Nike’s signature "Safari" print and splashes of Monarch and Chlorine Blue.

At the Electric Pack Olympic Safari Nike SB Dunk Low, The suede upper in Phantom serves as a low-key background for the tonal heel and forefoot overlays covered in Safari print’s iconic black speckles. The rubber cupsole, Swoosh logo, tongue, back tab, and collar come in black, while Monarch orange decorates the collar lining and appears on the heel tab’s ‘NIKE’ embroidery. Zoom Air cushioning in the insoles and padding around the tongue and collar further elevates this eye-catching sneaker.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of Chlorine Blue laces. They add a pop of color that makes this low-top sneaker live up to its "Electric" name. The Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari was released on August 9, 2024, and sold for $125.
